content: Welcome to the Online Renju Class theory lesson!
In the first place, this is my first teaching in the Renju Class. I am very glad to be teacher on the Renju Class.
So, let me introduce myself in few words.
I have been playing renju about 8 years ago. I started my renju career on Richard's PBEM server.
I live in capital city of Hungary, in Budapest. I am a teacher in University of E鰐v鰏 Lor醤d in Budapest on the Department of Inorganic and Analytical Chemistry.
Now, please press "I AM HERE" button, to show that you are here.

mayhem, endlessroad, bergamot, slamduk, scm2000, luwenzhe, casar, autickocz, Aurora, Xespok, liuwenming, shaoping, mcmanus, Intotherenju, swordblue, ushi, Silver, gobarka, yyfcsd, shuwang, span, moocheng, wolfzhou, zhp3410, callings, kongguyoulan, mikn1, sosei, ouyang, weigui, QBEN, ken_ro, FIFAWORLDCUP, NANYIN, H8, Chucky, coco_yuang, Renju_liu_t, HEX77.
Now, we are ready to begin. Today we will continue to study renju opening, called i4.
i4 opening was started past week, when teacher Shaoping presented black victory after easiest white 4th moves.

Today we will study next two white 4th moves: namely h6 and i6
In both cases, we will confirm black sure win.
We start with 4.h6 What is the best 5th move here?

Here, the best 5th move is i7. This variation transposes to the well known i7 opening pattern, so everything is easy here.
What is next best 5th move? Please answer!
i6 is the best, j6 also very strong
i6 also come from i8 opening
We will analyse some 6th moves here. i7 is key point here (because of best 5th move is i7) In most cases if black 7th move is played to i7, black will win easily.
Like this. Black creates three open lines!
And this one. Do you understand of idea 7. i7?
As an example, we choose this variant.

8. k7 is the best defence, black's 11th move creates very strong attacking base. 9th move can be played at K6, but after white has some tricky move. Who would like to show the win after this 12th move? Say ME!
Now, the 7. i7 is not working because white 6th move blocks black's i7_j7 pair. Understand?
This 17th move is very nice VCF threat, can everybody see it?
it seems h5 is only defense?
Yes h5 is only, but easy win....
What is the next black move here?
Yes i10. Who would like to show the victory here? Not easy. Say ME!
Then we need to check this 16th move.
22 and 24 are important. do you agree?
Who would like to show win here? Say ME!
Now, we will examine this 6th move. White killed black's key point!
This is the victory move! Who knows what is the well known opening that variant transposes to? We check now who has the bigest eyes :)
No need to ask, yyfcsd answer the question before :)
he always has the bigest eyes. ^^
Now, we investigate the strongest 6th move: K8
What is the strongest black move here?
G8 is the best, you answer well! Thx.
Black will now develop to the left side space, seems white can become active. But black 11th move will give answer for all questions! This move controll all white threats.
13. i10 is more stable move than 13. i7 !
Of course 13. i7 also lead black victory.
Yes, but muck harder job for black.
yes, i7 also win, but i10 more elegant
Who would like to show black win here? Say ME!
Maybe, it is interesting to check this 8th move. White tries to enclose black's material.
This is very strong fukumi move. Can you the see the VCF threat?

We continue with more difficult 4th move now: i6
What is the best 5th move in this situation? Please Answer!
Yes, the best move here is i7! i8 is questionable  move.

If white move here, the variant transposes to the opening i7.
Logical white 6th moves at K7 or J8 are also not too strong, so black can find the win easily.
We will prove black win here! This is strong defence.
This is very nice and logical sequence.
We change 6th move now, this is very strong defence.
Here, black cannot win with direct attack, beacuse white can cut!
This 11th yobi move gives sure win position for the black.
Now, black has two VCF threats, so can you see it?
one in left side one in right side
17th is a VFF threat, this move solves black's problem!
But what happens, if black chooses wrong 5th move???!!! Let's check it.
Here, the only good white defence is J10, other white moves result black wins.
But now, black cannot win beacuse of edge effect.
After long analysis, I did not find black win here!
What is the second best 5th move here? Please answer!
Yes, G8.  5. i5 is also very strong choice, but that is positional style. In my opinion, 5. g9 is similar strong than g8, but needs to investigate.
Firstly, we will check this 6th move.
Black loses the tempo, but white cannot attack now, and black is very strong in the left side.
This move is a VCF threat. Can everybody see it?
Strongest 22th, but black has a VCF!
Who can show us? Say ME!
These 6th and 7th moves are very frequent.
Logical Attack. Other white defences lose quickly.
Black wins! White cannot use his four.
Black builds very strong attacking base.
And then black has VCF. See it?
Black has VCF. Do you see it?
There are very logical and effective black moves!
19th is very important and nice move.
This is nice black yobi move! Only white defence here is 8. i8
Do you remember for this position? I hope so!!!
We continue with best white 6th move!
Old theory said that this was the best black sequence to warrant black victory.
But here white has strong defence, after long analysis, I did not find straight black win! Maybe black can win with positional style.
seems hard, not sloved in Ando's old theory lessons
So then, what is the best move here for black? Plese give some advice to poor black! :)
Please give some advice, i forgot best move here :))))
Yes H9! This move guarantees the sure win.
This is only white defence sequence, other white moves lose very quickly.
Who would like to try as black here? Say ME!
THX Mayhem! It was good job!
Do you remember about this very primitive black attack? :))) This type of attack is very effective!
Who will be the black here? Please say ME!
We finished strongest white defence after 4. i6
In conclusion, both 4th white moves (h6 and i6) lead black sure win.
But we need to revise old theories every time, because we can find some inaccuracies in the theory.
If we have big collection about these surprise white defences, we would easily shock our opponents in the real game! And our opponent cannot surpise us so easily!
So this 10th move is very surprise move.
who dont click the i am here botton?
Ando did not solved this variant in his lesson.
